{
  "texts": [
    "Departments of Community Mental Health (DCMH) are an integral part of the system of ISSN 2612-2138 mental health support in the armed forces of Great Britain.",
    "They include consultant psychiatrists, mental health nurses, mental health social workers and, where appropriate, clinical psychologists.",
    "The main purpose of these departments is to support members of the armed forces and refer them to inpatient treatment if necessary.",
    "The Veterans Health Alliance is also worth noting among other features of support for veterans in the health care system in Britain.",
    "It consists of 49 hospitals and ambulances in England, Scotland and Wales."
  ]
}